Accuracy

It is a decomposition of the accuracy, originally proposed by Story and Congalton (Story and Congalton 1986). * Producers’ accuracy (omission error) is how well a specific area on the Earth is mapped. It is the probability that a reference sample is correctly classified. * User’s accuracy (or reliability) is how well the map represents what is really on the ground.
